            <h2>Watch Party</h2>

            <p>
                This project was a year-long group project for my software engineering capstone sequence. We created an application called “Watch Party”, a social media platform for finding new shows or movies and engaging with friends and family through posts and reviews.
                We used ASP.NET Core as our main framework, alongside C#, JavaScript, SQL, Selenium and NUnit for testing, and Azure for database management and deployment. We worked in an agile environment, working in two-week sprints and using Jira as a management tool.
                I mainly worked on the profile and authorization, the watch lists, and the search details. I used Identity for authentication and utilized repository patterns to create a profile. The watch lists are where users can save shows and movies into three different lists, so they can keep track of shows that they have seen, want to watch, and are currently watching.
                The search details are where you can click on a search result and see more details about that show, along with some interesting pictures and displays.
                These last two pieces that I worked on both utilized the TMDB API to create the best user experience.
            </p>
