            <h2>Youth Risk Behavior</h2>
            <p>
                This is my final project for a Data Visualization class. I used Python as the main programming language.
                I chose to write my final project on youth risk behavior. The dataset that I used can be found <a href="https://chronicdata.cdc.gov/Youth-Risk-Behaviors/DASH-Youth-Risk-Behavior-Surveillance-System-YRBSS/q6p7-56au">here.</a>
                My first graphs show risky behavior for high school students based on different demographics.
                I made each of these a separate chart, so the user would be able to fully digest the information given on each one and see the differences between them all.
                My final chart is interactive, giving the user the ability to select different states/countries and see either the greater risk average, lesser risk average, or both.
                I enjoyed being able to learn how to effectively display data for the user, so that I can tell a story with such a large dataset.
            </p>
